runs.text:
Recipe:  Inject your chicken with a solution made up of...

2 sticks of butter = (1/2 lb.)
1/2 cup water
1 tsp. garlic powder
1 tsp. onion powder
1 tsp. black pepper
1/2 tsp. salt
1/2 tsp. lemon juice
Heat until butter melts (not super hot) then inject!

Rub the outside of the bird with your favorite poultry rub
or Cajun Seasoning......you almost can't use to much!  

Cook the bird in 350 degree oil 6 minutes per lb. 
Our 9 lb. chicken took us 55 minutes to hit 160 degrees inside.

After we took it in the house it still climbed up to 173 degrees.

Let the bird rest for 20 to 30 minutes then carve.   

You will fight over the crunchy skin!  Delicious ... Enjoy!

-~-~~-~~~-~~-~-

title.simpleText: Cooking with Shotgun Red

metadata.simpleText:
Welcome to Cooking with Shotgun Red!
Thanks for checking out our cooking channel! 

We do all kinds of easy and delicious recipes from Beef, Pork, Poultry, Fish, Seafood, Deserts, and Wild Game! 
We hope you find a recipe that you can share with your friends and family and get some great feedback at the table. 

This channel was created by the legendary Steve Hall creator of Shotgun Red. Steve passed away in December 2018 but with the help of his longtime parter Miss Sheila and his longtime friend, vocalist from his show, Jennifer Bruce, we are still releasing fun and delicious recipes! Steve would be so happy knowing his channel continues to grow and live on.

We really hope you subscribe to our channel! Follow us on Facebook and join our free membership at our website below.

Thanks for watching and supporting us ... Steve Hall / Miss Sheila / Jennifer Bruce / Shotgun Red
